00:28:25.810 --> 00:28:27.370 align:middle line:90%
and we're all love.

00:28:27.370 --> 00:28:31.520 align:middle line:84%
This energy is intelligent,
and its purpose is love.

00:28:31.520 --> 00:28:34.450 align:middle line:84%
But I generally believe that we
come into this physical plane

00:28:34.450 --> 00:28:37.140 align:middle line:84%
to experience, to
play, to have fun,

00:28:37.140 --> 00:28:39.630 align:middle line:84%
to learn, and to
share, and to help

00:28:39.630 --> 00:28:42.390 align:middle line:84%
other-- in telling the
souls of the beings

00:28:42.390 --> 00:28:43.960 align:middle line:90%
on this physical plane.

00:28:43.960 --> 00:28:47.870 align:middle line:84%
So every single
person comes here,

00:28:47.870 --> 00:28:50.220 align:middle line:84%
and when we shuffle
off this mortal coil,

00:28:50.220 --> 00:28:51.950 align:middle line:90%
we go onto something else.

00:28:51.950 --> 00:28:53.870 align:middle line:84%
And whatever that
is, what I know

00:28:53.870 --> 00:28:56.720 align:middle line:84%
is that we all have the ability
therefore to be whatever

00:28:56.720 --> 00:28:58.480 align:middle line:90%
you want to be in this world.

00:28:58.480 --> 00:29:03.660 align:middle line:10%
So we come here with a call
to us, but you put it really,

00:29:03.660 --> 00:29:07.590 align:middle line:10%
really well when you
say, the world conspires

00:29:07.590 --> 00:29:10.100 align:middle line:10%
to hold us against ourselves.

00:29:10.100 --> 00:29:14.450 align:middle line:10%
The adverse, the teaching,
the newspapers, the economy

00:29:14.450 --> 00:29:16.220 align:middle line:10%
conspires to have
us not be there.

00:29:16.220 --> 00:29:19.110 align:middle line:84%
And we start defending
ourselves because our true self

00:29:19.110 --> 00:29:20.600 align:middle line:90%
is with us as a baby.

00:29:20.600 --> 00:29:21.975 align:middle line:84%
It's with us as
young child, and do

00:29:21.975 --> 00:29:24.500 align:middle line:84%
we notice as we get
to teenage years,

00:29:24.500 --> 00:29:26.720 align:middle line:90%
we start defending ourselves?

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:30.940 align:middle line:10%
And the real fall for us all
comes when we stop defending

00:29:30.940 --> 00:29:33.840 align:middle line:10%
ourselves, and we give
in, and we become what we

00:29:33.840 --> 00:29:35.680 align:middle line:10%
think the world wants us to be.

00:29:35.680 --> 00:29:37.540 align:middle line:10%
And that's what I call non-self.

00:29:37.540 --> 00:29:40.880 align:middle line:10%
And in non-self, you can't truly
be happy because inside of you,

00:29:40.880 --> 00:29:43.380 align:middle line:10%
inside of all of us, we
know there's something else

00:29:43.380 --> 00:29:44.890 align:middle line:10%
there that's really true to us.

00:29:44.890 --> 00:29:53.090 align:middle line:10%
So I'm guided to help others to
find that place inside of them

00:29:53.090 --> 00:29:56.390 align:middle line:10%
and then have the courage
because it's all well and good

00:29:56.390 --> 00:29:59.470 align:middle line:10%
saying to someone, find
yourself and be your true self,

00:29:59.470 --> 00:30:04.530 align:middle line:10%
but it's difficult isn't
it in the real world when

00:30:04.530 --> 00:30:06.050 align:middle line:10%
people saying, well,
to criticize you

00:30:06.050 --> 00:30:07.290 align:middle line:10%
and observe what you're doing.

00:30:07.290 --> 00:30:10.170 align:middle line:84%
And they would say,
what are you doing?

00:30:10.170 --> 00:30:12.360 align:middle line:84%
You might feel
embarrassed or humiliated

00:30:12.360 --> 00:30:14.620 align:middle line:84%
or strange or
different or crazy,

00:30:14.620 --> 00:30:18.850 align:middle line:84%
but you know, when
this life ends,

00:30:18.850 --> 00:30:21.020 align:middle line:84%
all that will mean
nothing at all.

00:30:21.020 --> 00:30:22.730 align:middle line:84%
What really will have
mattered did you get

00:30:22.730 --> 00:30:25.100 align:middle line:90%
your internal expression out?

00:30:25.100 --> 00:30:27.680 align:middle line:84%
You did you get your
true self into the world?

00:30:27.680 --> 00:30:32.210 align:middle line:84%
Who'd want to be on their death
bed at 102 and at that point

00:30:32.210 --> 00:30:34.400 align:middle line:84%
be saying to themselves,
I didn't quite

00:30:34.400 --> 00:30:36.010 align:middle line:90%
get myself into the world.

00:30:36.010 --> 00:30:37.090 align:middle line:90%
I didn't quite live my life.

00:30:37.090 --> 00:30:38.740 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I'm going
onto who knows

00:30:38.740 --> 00:30:40.800 align:middle line:84%
where, knowing that
when I came here with

00:30:40.800 --> 00:30:42.240 align:middle line:90%
is still inside of me.

00:30:42.240 --> 00:30:45.840 align:middle line:84%
We want to get that thing, our
true self, outside of ourselves

00:30:45.840 --> 00:30:47.940 align:middle line:90%
and express that in the world.

00:30:47.940 --> 00:30:51.340 align:middle line:84%
So for all of us, and
certainly for me and people

00:30:51.340 --> 00:30:53.960 align:middle line:84%
I've worked with and
coached and spoken four,

00:30:53.960 --> 00:30:57.550 align:middle line:84%
it became, well,
how do I do this.

00:30:57.550 --> 00:31:02.170 align:middle line:84%
So I remember
those-- Steven Jobs.

00:31:02.170 --> 00:31:05.500 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, and Steven Jobs
founded Apple and Pixar,

00:31:05.500 --> 00:31:09.320 align:middle line:84%
and he did the Stanford
address a few years ago.

00:31:09.320 --> 00:31:10.480 align:middle line:10%
And I know that
Stanford address,

00:31:10.480 --> 00:31:12.710 align:middle line:10%
I thought it was really
interesting what he said

00:31:12.710 --> 00:31:15.940 align:middle line:10%
and also what he didn't
say because as he did this,

00:31:15.940 --> 00:31:17.300 align:middle line:10%
he made this address.

00:31:17.300 --> 00:31:21.240 align:middle line:10%
And he said, well, let's look
at some of the facts, one

00:31:21.240 --> 00:31:24.530 align:middle line:10%
of the world's richest men,
one of the most creative men

00:31:24.530 --> 00:31:27.330 align:middle line:10%
in the world, and pretty
much, at that point addressing

00:31:27.330 --> 00:31:30.270 align:middle line:10%
the Stanford graduating class,
had the world and the future

00:31:30.270 --> 00:31:32.180 align:middle line:10%
of the world-- they
call it the [INAUDIBLE]

00:31:32.180 --> 00:31:34.660 align:middle line:84%
and the whys of the world
in his hands, in his grasp.

00:31:34.660 --> 00:31:37.030 align:middle line:84%
But let's look at
what he actually did.

00:31:37.030 --> 00:31:39.300 align:middle line:10%
What he actually did,
he told three stories

00:31:39.300 --> 00:31:42.630 align:middle line:10%
about his life, three stories.

00:31:42.630 --> 00:31:44.420 align:middle line:84%
He didn't give a
business process.

00:31:44.420 --> 00:31:47.157 align:middle line:84%
He didn't say, follow
this model, XYZ, 1 on 1--

00:31:47.157 --> 00:31:47.990 align:middle line:90%
he didn't do any of that.

00:31:47.990 --> 00:31:49.510 align:middle line:84%
He gave three
stories of his life,

00:31:49.510 --> 00:31:51.780 align:middle line:84%
and then he said-- and I'm
paraphrasing-- and he said,

00:31:51.780 --> 00:31:54.330 align:middle line:84%
there's something inside
of you that knows you

00:31:54.330 --> 00:31:56.500 align:middle line:84%
better than you know yourself.
It's you heart.

00:31:56.500 --> 00:31:58.550 align:middle line:84%
It's your intuition,
and to follow

00:31:58.550 --> 00:31:59.660 align:middle line:90%
that heart and intuition.

00:31:59.660 --> 00:32:03.190 align:middle line:84%
To learn to drown out the
outer voices, the voice

00:32:03.190 --> 00:32:04.700 align:middle line:84%
that would confuse
you, and to pay

00:32:04.700 --> 00:32:07.170 align:middle line:90%
attention to the inner voice.

00:32:07.170 --> 00:32:10.240 align:middle line:84%
And he also said
that in his life,

00:32:10.240 --> 00:32:14.100 align:middle line:84%
listening to the inner voice,
it has never let him down.

00:32:14.100 --> 00:32:16.106 align:middle line:84%
He had always been
guided by that.

00:32:16.106 --> 00:32:18.340 align:middle line:10%
Now that's all sounds
wonderful and great,

00:32:18.340 --> 00:32:20.140 align:middle line:10%
and I can accept that.

00:32:20.140 --> 00:32:23.690 align:middle line:84%
What I think the bigger message
is that he said that instead

00:32:23.690 --> 00:32:26.460 align:middle line:84%
of a business model for success,
that he said that in terms

00:32:26.460 --> 00:32:28.380 align:middle line:84%
of how to be happy and
find out who you are,

00:32:28.380 --> 00:32:30.030 align:middle line:84%
that he said that in
terms of a message

00:32:30.030 --> 00:32:33.080 align:middle line:84%
to people that are in
their heads, the academics.

00:32:33.080 --> 00:32:34.760 align:middle line:10%
He said that was the message.

00:32:34.760 --> 00:32:35.770 align:middle line:10%
Find yourself.

00:32:35.770 --> 00:32:36.760 align:middle line:10%
It's your story.

00:32:36.760 --> 00:32:37.990 align:middle line:10%
This is your path.

00:32:37.990 --> 00:32:39.090 align:middle line:10%
Here are my three stories.

00:32:39.090 --> 00:32:41.110 align:middle line:10%
Here's my path, and
here's what you can do.

00:32:41.110 --> 00:32:42.580 align:middle line:90%
It's your inner self.

00:32:42.580 --> 00:32:44.390 align:middle line:84%
So when I picked
upon that, which

00:32:44.390 --> 00:32:46.555 align:middle line:84%
was only last November,
because obviously it

00:32:46.555 --> 00:32:47.900 align:middle line:90%
was after his death.

