in Indonesia last week

00:35:21.130 --> 00:35:27.660 align:middle line:84%
to some agents and wealth
managers from Jakarta and Bali,

00:35:27.660 --> 00:35:31.150 align:middle line:84%
and I was blessed in
June to be able to speak

00:35:31.150 --> 00:35:35.120 align:middle line:90%
to 7,000 people in Anaheim.

00:35:35.120 --> 00:35:37.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's great because
you get the opportunity

00:35:37.490 --> 00:35:39.850 align:middle line:84%
to change lives and
give people another way

00:35:39.850 --> 00:35:41.070 align:middle line:90%
of looking at things.

00:35:41.070 --> 00:35:43.250 align:middle line:84%
People have a philosophy of
goals and what they can do.

00:35:43.250 --> 00:35:45.820 align:middle line:84%
But I want to wake up the
philosophy inside of a person,

00:35:45.820 --> 00:35:48.510 align:middle line:84%
to have them go internal and
go, OK, where's my genius?

00:35:48.510 --> 00:35:50.630 align:middle line:90%
What's the philosophy for me?

00:35:50.630 --> 00:35:52.872 align:middle line:90%
So that's what I speak to do.

00:35:52.872 --> 00:35:55.450 align:middle line:84%
I was perfectly on
time in that I feel.

00:35:55.450 --> 00:35:59.030 align:middle line:84%
Well it is at your own--
there are multiple numbers

00:35:59.030 --> 00:36:00.460 align:middle line:84%
of philosophies for
happiness and success

00:36:00.460 --> 00:36:04.550 align:middle line:84%
because there are multiple
people on this planet.

00:36:04.550 --> 00:36:08.740 align:middle line:84%
But I remember when
I was 13 years old,

00:36:08.740 --> 00:36:11.110 align:middle line:84%
and I just ran home
from school one day.

00:36:11.110 --> 00:36:14.250 align:middle line:84%
And I kind of ran into the
door like it was half open,

00:36:14.250 --> 00:36:16.760 align:middle line:84%
and as I looking
around the house,

00:36:16.760 --> 00:36:19.610 align:middle line:84%
there are members of my family
and friends and people there.

00:36:19.610 --> 00:36:21.630 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know
what was going on.

00:36:21.630 --> 00:36:23.900 align:middle line:84%
And people weren't speaking,
and it was all quiet,

00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:25.960 align:middle line:90%
and it was just after school.

00:36:25.960 --> 00:36:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that,
in a few moments,

00:36:27.260 --> 00:36:29.290 align:middle line:84%
my mother would be coming
because she gets home

00:36:29.290 --> 00:36:31.190 align:middle line:90%
from work around that time.

00:36:31.190 --> 00:36:33.940 align:middle line:84%
So I looked out the window,
and I was waiting for the bus

00:36:33.940 --> 00:36:34.990 align:middle line:90%
to come.

00:36:34.990 --> 00:36:38.280 align:middle line:84%
And her bus came and went, and
she didn't get off the bus.

00:36:38.280 --> 00:36:41.420 align:middle line:84%
So as I'm wondering were
she is and why she's late,

00:36:41.420 --> 00:36:44.810 align:middle line:84%
one of the neighbors burst
into the house and shouted,

00:36:44.810 --> 00:36:46.690 align:middle line:90%
Mavis is dead.

00:36:46.690 --> 00:36:54.370 align:middle line:84%
Mavis is dead, and that was
my mom my mother's pet name.

00:36:54.370 --> 00:36:56.430 align:middle line:84%
Her real name is
Kathleen [INAUDIBLE]

00:36:56.430 --> 00:37:00.580 align:middle line:84%
Mills, but at 13, that's how
I found out that she died.

00:37:00.580 --> 00:37:04.440 align:middle line:84%
And what I can tell
you is that night--

00:37:04.440 --> 00:37:07.020 align:middle line:84%
one thing I knew for sure
is I didn't believe it.

00:37:07.020 --> 00:37:07.870 align:middle line:90%
I was in denial.

00:37:07.870 --> 00:37:09.500 align:middle line:84%
I did not believe
that she was dead,

00:37:09.500 --> 00:37:13.090 align:middle line:84%
and I remember going to bed
that night and sitting by my bed

00:37:13.090 --> 00:37:15.960 align:middle line:84%
and hugging the bed and
crying and praying that it was

00:37:15.960 --> 00:37:18.920 align:middle line:90%
just a dream or some mistake.

00:37:18.920 --> 00:37:21.460 align:middle line:84%
When I work up in the
morning, it wasn't a dream.

00:37:21.460 --> 00:37:26.050 align:middle line:84%
It was real, and I
knew that she was dead.

00:37:26.050 --> 00:37:29.870 align:middle line:84%
But two weeks after the
funeral, I still haven't spoken,

00:37:29.870 --> 00:37:32.060 align:middle line:84%
and I found that
I couldn't speak.

00:37:32.060 --> 00:37:36.230 align:middle line:84%
So ultimately, it was time for
us all to go back to school.

00:37:36.230 --> 00:37:39.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm one of seven children, but
it's time to go back to school,

00:37:39.390 --> 00:37:40.720 align:middle line:90%
and we all went back to school.

00:37:40.720 --> 00:37:43.850 align:middle line:84%
And as fate would have
it, I sat in the classroom

00:37:43.850 --> 00:37:45.040 align:middle line:90%
that first day.

00:37:45.040 --> 00:37:47.930 align:middle line:84%
It's one of those days where
the teacher has a reading book,

00:37:47.930 --> 00:37:49.990 align:middle line:84%
and everyone has to take a
turn to read from the book,

00:37:49.990 --> 00:37:52.070 align:middle line:84%
and it came to my
turn from the book.

00:37:52.070 --> 00:37:55.430 align:middle line:84%
And as I looked to the book and
I tried to read, all I could do

00:37:55.430 --> 00:38:02.830 align:middle line:84%
was there was, ka--
ka-- and I managed

00:38:02.830 --> 00:38:05.962 align:middle line:84%
to blurt out that
I couldn't speak,

00:38:05.962 --> 00:38:07.790 align:middle line:84%
and I just buried
my head in my hands.

00:38:07.790 --> 00:38:10.520 align:middle line:84%
And what I remember,
even now, was

00:38:10.520 --> 00:38:14.000 align:middle line:84%
children laughing
around me, whispers

00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:17.780 align:middle line:90%
and mummers going around me.

00:38:17.780 --> 00:38:19.800 align:middle line:84%
Me not wanting to be
there because what

00:38:19.800 --> 00:38:22.145 align:middle line:84%
I'd realized that my
mother's death had done.

00:38:22.145 --> 00:38:24.090 align:middle line:84%
It was such a trauma to
me that it had given me

00:38:24.090 --> 00:38:30.074 align:middle line:84%
this amazingly bad
stutter or stammer,

00:38:30.074 --> 00:38:31.240 align:middle line:84%
and it meant that
I couldn't speak.

00:38:31.240 --> 00:38:34.580 align:middle line:10%
When I spoke, it was awful.

00:38:34.580 --> 00:38:38.030 align:middle line:84%
And from that point on, I
spoke with a huge embarrassing

00:38:38.030 --> 00:38:39.260 align:middle line:90%
stammer and stutter.

00:38:39.260 --> 00:38:41.840 align:middle line:84%
Couldn't get my words
out, couldn't articulate.

00:38:41.840 --> 00:38:42.540 align:middle line:90%
And that--

00:38:42.540 --> 00:38:44.050 align:middle line:90%
It's hard to believe.

00:38:44.050 --> 00:38:48.230 align:middle line:84%
Well, that stayed with me
right through my teenage years.

00:38:48.230 --> 00:38:51.430 align:middle line:84%
And you know how cruel children
can be when you have a stutter.

00:38:51.430 --> 00:38:53.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, even in college
I had a nickname,

00:38:53.500 --> 00:38:55.750 align:middle line:84%
and I was nicknamed
the stuttering parrot.

00:38:55.750 --> 00:38:58.660 align:middle line:84%
That was my friends,
so it was a--

00:38:58.660 --> 00:39:00.880 align:middle line:90%
Your friends [INAUDIBLE].

00:39:00.880 --> 00:39:05.210 align:middle line:84%
Exactly, and actually it
wasn't until my mid-twenties

00:39:05.210 --> 00:39:09.046 align:middle line:84%
when things changed because,
and again, I realize now

00:39:09.046 --> 00:39:10.410 align:middle line:90%
it was one of those moments.

00:39:10.410 --> 00:39:12.610 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't call it a
10-second moment them.

00:39:12.610 --> 00:39:15.240 align:middle line:84%
A moment I was in
the office one day,

00:39:15.240 --> 00:39:18.935 align:middle line:84%
and again, the universe
collaborating ways we

00:39:18.935 --> 00:39:20.290 align:middle line:90%
can't always understand.

00:39:20.290 --> 00:39:22.902 align:middle line:84%
And the meaning isn't
always obvious in that time.

00:39:22.902 --> 00:39:24.735 align:middle line:84%
Because many times, we have
things happen in our lives,

00:39:24.735 --> 00:39:27.070 align:middle line:84%
and we say, well, that means
that, and that means that.

00:39:27.070 --> 00:39:28.460 align:middle line:90%
Well, it may not mean that.

00:39:28.460 --> 00:39:29.880 align:middle line:84%
The meaning could
be 20 years later,

00:39:29.880 --> 00:39:31.495 align:middle line:84%
or the meaning could
not be for you at all.

00:39:31.495 --> 00:39:33.095 align:middle line:84%
It could be for another
soul, for another spirit

00:39:33.095 --> 00:39:34.500 align:middle line:90%
for somebody else.

00:39:34.500 --> 00:39:39.810 align:middle line:84%
So one day I'm in the office,
and the owner of the business

00:39:39.810 --> 00:39:43.020 align:middle line:84%
asked me to introduced him to a
bunch of new potential recruits

00:39:43.020 --> 00:39:44.070 align:middle line:90%
in the office.

00:39:44.070 --> 00:39:46.052 align:middle line:84%
And I said actually, you know,
obviously I can't do this.

00:39:46.052 --> 00:39:47.677 align:middle line:90%
You know I can't do this I said.

00:39:47.677 --> 00:39:48.910 align:middle line:84%
He said, well,
there's no one around.

00:39:48.910 --> 00:39:51.390 align:middle line:84%
Everyone is out seeing
clients and just prospecting.

00:39:51.390 --> 00:39:53.160 align:middle line:84%
And you're the only
one in the office.

00:39:53.160 --> 00:39:55.160 align:middle line:90%
You need to do this.

00:39:55.160 --> 00:39:57.850 align:middle line:84%
So I went into this room
with only about 16 people,

00:39:57.850 --> 00:40:00.570 align:middle line:84%
and they're all potential
recruits for the company.

00:40:00.570 --> 00:40:02.470 align:middle line:84%
And I actually don't
know what I said.

00:40:02.470 --> 00:40:04.000 align:middle line:84%
Even now I don't
know what I said.

00:40:04.000 --> 00:40:06.020 align:middle line:84%
What I do know is
that I stammered.

00:40:06.020 --> 00:40:07.270 align:middle line:90%
I stuttered.

00:40:07.270 --> 00:40:10.840 align:middle line:84%
I sweated, spluttered,
and eventually I

00:40:10.840 --> 00:40:14.280 align:middle line:84%
looked for the door, and I said,
Dennis, through the glass door.

00:40:14.280 --> 00:40:16.430 align:middle line:84%
And he took my note,
and he came in the room.

00:40:16.430 --> 00:40:20.020 align:middle line:84%
And I had to sit there for the
whole hour and a half or so

00:40:20.020 --> 00:40:22.670 align:middle line:84%
with humiliation knowing
that everyone in the room

00:40:22.670 --> 00:40:24.870 align:middle line:90%
know how badly I performed.

00:40:24.870 --> 00:40:27.252 align:middle line:84%
So but that wasn't
the end of it.

00:40:27.252 --> 00:40:28.190 align:middle line:90%
I thought that was over.

00:40:28.190 --> 00:40:29.640 align:middle line:84%
You know how you've
been to those places

00:40:29.640 --> 00:40:32.050 align:middle line:84%
where you're hoping that
there will be an emergency.

00:40:32.050 --> 00:40:33.240 align:middle line:84%
You're hoping the
phone will ring

00:40:33.240 --> 00:40:34.657 align:middle line:84%
and someone will get
you out of the room,

00:40:34.657 --> 00:40:35.490 align:middle line:90%
but there's no emergency.

00:40:35.490 --> 00:40:37.624 align:middle line:84%
You have to stay in the room for
the whole of this presentation.

00:40:37.624 --> 00:40:38.323 align:middle line:90%
That is the thing.

00:40:38.323 --> 00:40:39.710 align:middle line:84%
We always think we're
going to be saved.

00:40:39.710 --> 00:40:42.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, great.
Really good.

00:40:42.120 --> 00:40:43.020 align:middle line:90%
I like that.

00:40:43.020 --> 00:40:46.490 align:middle line:84%
And two weeks later,
I'm in the office.

00:40:46.490 --> 00:40:48.250 align:middle line:90%
I'm only a junior at the time.

00:40:48.250 --> 00:40:50.590 align:middle line:84%
I'm in the office,
and I get a letter

00:40:50.590 --> 00:40:51.740 align:middle line:90%
addressed to me personally.

00:40:51.740 --> 00:40:53.580 align:middle line:84%
And the letter was
from a young lady

00:40:53.580 --> 00:40:56.440 align:middle line:84%
who had been in that small
group of potential recruits.

00:40:56.440 --> 00:40:57.240 align:middle line:90%
And she explained to me.

00:40:57.240 --> 00:40:59.490 align:middle line:84%
She said that she didn't
get a job or a position

00:40:59.490 --> 00:41:01.180 align:middle line:90%
as a trainee with the company.

00:41:01.180 --> 00:41:03.700 align:middle line:84%
And she mentioned she had this
experience and that experience

00:41:03.700 --> 00:41:05.820 align:middle line:84%
and that qualification
and she finished

00:41:05.820 --> 00:41:07.490 align:middle line:84%
off the letter by
saying, I didn't

00:41:07.490 --> 00:41:08.430 align:middle line:90%
get the job Mr. [INAUDIBLE].

00:41:08.430 --> 00:41:10.970 align:middle line:84%
I can't understand how I didn't
get the job when someone like

00:41:10.970 --> 00:41:12.680 align:middle line:84%
you who can't even
speak properly

00:41:12.680 --> 00:41:16.510 align:middle line:84%
and who babbled incoherently
can be in the company,

00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:17.690 align:middle line:90%
and I couldn't.

00:41:17.690 --> 00:41:19.030 align:middle line:90%
And that was her letter.

00:41:19.030 --> 00:41:21.400 align:middle line:84%
And what I know is
that in that moment

00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:22.765 align:middle line:84%
in the open planned
office because that

00:41:22.765 --> 00:41:24.450 align:middle line:90%
was two weeks later.

00:41:24.450 --> 00:41:27.535 align:middle line:84%
Bizarre, as it may sound, I kind
of new in that moment, everyone

00:41:27.535 --> 00:41:29.330 align:middle line:90%
could read my mind.

00:41:29.330 --> 00:41:31.570 align:middle line:10%
[INAUDIBLE] I can't read this
letter again because if I do,

00:41:31.570 --> 00:41:34.180 align:middle line:10%
they'll all pick up
on my humiliation.

00:41:34.180 --> 00:41:36.670 align:middle line:84%
So I screwed the letter up,
and I threw it in a basked

00:41:36.670 --> 00:41:37.980 align:middle line:90%
beneath my desk.

00:41:37.980 --> 00:41:43.220 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is, regardless
of her intention for writing

00:41:43.220 --> 00:41:46.170 align:middle line:90%
that letter, she was right.

00:41:46.170 --> 00:41:47.900 align:middle line:10%
I knew that I couldn't
speak properly,

00:41:47.900 --> 00:41:51.170 align:middle line:10%
so I made a commitment that
day to learn to speak again

00:41:51.170 --> 00:41:52.530 align:middle line:10%
for a second time,
to learn to speak

00:41:52.530 --> 00:41:54.210 align:middle line:10%
properly for a second time.

00:41:54.210 --> 00:41:54.950 align:middle line:10%
So I did that.

00:41:54.950 --> 00:41:56.190 align:middle line:10%
Went on speaking courses.

00:41:56.190 --> 00:41:59.260 align:middle line:10%
Went on Dale Carnegie
course over 14 weeks.

00:41:59.260 --> 00:42:04.100 align:middle line:10%
And starting off, let's just say
stuttering, stuttering starts,

00:42:04.100 --> 00:42:06.940 align:middle line:10%
and by end of that
14-week program,

00:42:06.940 --> 00:42:11.025 align:middle line:10%
I had emerged as the person
with the most improvement.

00:42:11.025 --> 00:42:12.140 align:middle line:10%
I didn't become a speaker.

00:42:12.140 --> 00:42:13.570 align:middle line:10%
That was when I was 25.

00:42:13.570 --> 00:42:15.890 align:middle line:10%
I didn't become a speaker
until two years ago,

00:42:15.890 --> 00:42:20.790 align:middle line:10%
as in professional speaker
because when I changed my life

00:42:20.790 --> 00:42:23.310 align:middle line:10%
around, so many people
kept turning up and saying,

00:42:23.310 --> 00:42:24.180 align:middle line:10%
what do you do?

00:42:24.180 --> 00:42:25.030 align:middle line:90%
Share with us?

00:42:25.030 --> 00:42:26.659 align:middle line:84%
Talk to me about standards.
I've had goals.

00:42:26.659 --> 00:42:27.510 align:middle line:90%
I'm still not happy.

00:42:27.510 --> 00:42:31.090 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, I had
a second awakening.

00:42:31.090 --> 00:42:32.650 align:middle line:84%
So that question
by a security guard

00:42:32.650 --> 00:42:36.216 align:middle line:84%
was really just the first
awa-- I woke up and found who

00:42:36.216 --> 00:42:40.070 align:middle line:84%
I really was that took
me out of my unhappiness

00:42:40.070 --> 00:42:42.280 align:middle line:90%
in a financial position.

00:42:42.280 --> 00:42:46.370 align:middle line:84%
The second awakening came
in 2010 where I realized

00:42:46.370 --> 00:42:48.020 align:middle line:90%
this isn't just for me.

00:42:48.020 --> 00:42:50.060 align:middle line:84%
These people have been turning
up over the last few years.

00:42:50.060 --> 00:42:51.040 align:middle line:90%
It's not just me.

00:42:51.040 --> 00:42:55.500 align:middle line:84%
It's me to share what came out
to my true self with the world,

00:42:55.500 --> 00:42:59.660 align:middle line:84%
so I am, at that point,
in the June, 2010, went

00:42:59.660 --> 00:43:02.980 align:middle line:84%
along to a small chapter of
the professional speaking

00:43:02.980 --> 00:43:03.985 align:middle line:90%
association.

00:43:03.985 --> 00:43:06.200 align:middle line:84%
It was a 10-minute
showcase to share

00:43:06.200 --> 00:43:08.520 align:middle line:84%
my philosophy of
standards and set of goals

00:43:08.520 --> 00:43:09.940 align:middle line:90%
and share my story.

00:43:09.940 --> 00:43:15.010 align:middle line:10%
And they gave me such
an amazing welcome,

00:43:15.010 --> 00:43:19.820 align:middle line:10%
and it was humbling, the
response that they gave me.

00:43:19.820 --> 00:43:22.260 align:middle line:84%
And I really felt,
yeah, I'm doing this.

00:43:22.260 --> 00:43:26.125 align:middle line:84%
But I'm the kind of
person where kind of I

00:43:26.125 --> 00:43:27.830 align:middle line:84%
still wanted to
test it some more.

00:43:27.830 --> 00:43:30.000 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not saying I had
a massive external frame

00:43:30.000 --> 00:43:32.530 align:middle line:84%
of reference, but I did want
to test and see whether, are

00:43:32.530 --> 00:43:33.380 align:middle line:90%
they just being kind.

00:43:33.380 --> 00:43:34.130 align:middle line:90%
They're lovely people.

00:43:34.130 --> 00:43:35.860 align:middle line:90%
Are they just being nice?

00:43:35.860 --> 00:43:38.750 align:middle line:84%
And so I then applied to
speak at the global speaker

00:43:38.750 --> 00:43:41.770 align:middle line:90%
summit, which was last April.

00:43:41.770 --> 00:43:43.750 align:middle line:84%
And I said, actually,
no, you can't

00:43:43.750 --> 00:43:45.935 align:middle line:84%
speak at that because it's
being booked for a year ahead.

00:43:45.935 --> 00:43:47.275 align:middle line:90%
Also, because it's booked.

00:43:47.275 --> 00:43:50.250 align:middle line:84%
But something inside me
just said, check again.

00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:53.570 align:middle line:84%
So I checked again last
January, no response.

00:43:53.570 --> 00:43:56.660 align:middle line:84%
Checked again last February with
an email, and I emailed saying,

00:43:56.660 --> 00:43:57.360 align:middle line:90%
could I speak.

00:43:57.360 --> 00:43:58.740 align:middle line:90%
Has anybody dropped out.

00:43:58.740 --> 00:44:00.950 align:middle line:84%
An email came back
within minutes saying,

00:44:00.950 --> 00:44:02.760 align:middle line:90%
someone just dropped out.

00:44:02.760 --> 00:44:03.980 align:middle line:84%
What would you like
to speak about.

00:44:03.980 --> 00:44:06.920 align:middle line:84%
Long story short, I ended up
speaking at the global speaker

00:44:06.920 --> 00:44:09.510 align:middle line:84%
summit last April
in front of a room

00:44:09.510 --> 00:44:12.380 align:middle line:84%
full of international
speakers and coaches whatever,

00:44:12.380 --> 00:44:13.980 align:middle line:84%
and they gave me
such an innovation

00:44:13.980 --> 00:44:17.120 align:middle line:84%
at the end that I knew
I had got something

00:44:17.120 --> 00:44:18.880 align:middle line:84%
because it's a
